Hi everyone!  I'm happy to announce the release of KSP Trajectory Optimization Tool v1.5.1!  This release has been a long time coming with the last previous release occurring last year.  The main purpose of this release is KSP 1.1.x compatibility with the KSPTOTConnect plugin.  Other bug fixes are present in the code too, both in the KSPTOTConnect code and in the standalone MATLAB-based code.

The download link is present in the first post of this thread.  Follow the download instructions to install.  If you're coming from KSPTOT v1.5.1, all you need to do is replace the KSPTOTConnect plugin and then replace the KSPTOT *.exe file and associated files.

Please let me know if you find any bugs or issues.  Happy orbiting!

The issue is that the name of the body has spaces in it, which messes with some internal data structures.  I'll fix this for next time.  Thanks for the report!  EDIT: So there were a number of problems: spaces, special characters in names, etc.  I think I have a fix for next version, but in the mean time, you can just go through the bodies.ini file and either remove what you don't need or make sure that all the names of bodies are strictly numbers and letters without special characters or spaces.  If you change the name of a body, make sure you update parent name on all its children to match the new name.

Reproduction:

Load up the file in Mission Achitect.

Open up optimization.

The only optimization events should be the second "Coast" to a correction burn and the Correction burn itself.  I leave the objective function on Distance to Body, select event 6: Coast to Duna as the applicable event and the applicable body is Duna.  I then choose the optimization constraint "Radius of Periapsis" with the right arrow.  It opens up the dialog box.

I enter 50km lower bound, 100km upper bound, Duna as the celestial body and the applicable event is still Event 6: Coast to Duna.

I then click "Save and Close" at which point Windows beeps at me and the window fails to close.  Clicking the "X" to close the window manually shows that the constraint is not added.

Note: I built this mission in the last release version of KSPTOT.  In that version, I can add constraints just fine.

Here's mine: https://drive.google.com/open?id=0B7AaFFbHPo5MVnVLaFh6MUlrbGc
